The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
		 Sunday, January 11, 2004  BRIEFS
				 																																	Kaliachak (Malda), Jan. 10: Ten people were injured this afternoon when villagers clashed with BSF jawans who had seized 200 cows, alleging attempts at smuggling the cattle to Bangladesh.				 																																	The villagers gheraoed the jawans, demanding that the cows be released. They attacked the jawans with bamboo sticks and snatched two rifle and two magazines from them. The BSF personnel then fired in the open, injuring 10 villagers.				 																																	Bandel: A physician at a local pharmacy, Tapas Hazra, was arrested on Saturday evening for allegedly duping patients by identifying himself as an eye surgeon of a Barrackpore hospital, said police. 				 																																	Howrah: Three miscreants shot Moloy Chowdhury, a stationary shop owner, in his arm and leg on Saturday night when he rejected their demands for money. They also shot his wife in her abdomen when she rushed to save him.
